<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3><strong>Higher Education in Andhra Pradesh</strong></h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The higher education in AP is vast with number of universities, autonomous colleges, degree colleges and professional colleges. Apart from courses in conventional areas like arts, science, commerce, and courses in professional areas such as engineering, pharmacy, medicine, management, hotel management, etc. The top universities are:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>Andhra University</li><li>Sri Venkateswara University</li><li>Koneru Lakshmaiah Education Foundation University</li><li>Gandhi Institute of Technology and Management</li><li>Sri Sathya Sai Institute of Higher Learning</li><li>Vignan’s Foundation for Science, Technology and Research</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3><strong>Universities in AP</strong></h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Andhra Pradesh State has 53 universities. There are 3 central universities, 24 state universities, 3 private universities and 5 deemed universities. Some of the university names are given here:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>Central University of Andhra Pradesh</li><li>Indian Culinary Institute, Tirupati</li><li>Acharya Nagarjuna University</li><li>Sri Venkateswara Vedic University</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Through all these universities, government schools and private schools, colleges the quality of Education in Andhra Pradesh is improving day by day. So that, there is an improvement in the literacy rate. Education Minister of AP, Mr Srinivas Rao is also trying to get the ranked 1 in literacy rate in India.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->
